{"id":5,"date":"2016-03-30T12:28:09","date_gmt":"2016-03-30T16:28:09","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/standard-template.blog.yorku.ca\/?page_id=5"},"modified":"2022-06-01T10:07:17","modified_gmt":"2022-06-01T14:07:17","slug":"first-page","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/arms.info.yorku.ca\/","title":{"rendered":"Welcome to Academic Resource Management System (ARMS)"},"content":{"rendered":"<p align=\"justify\">The <strong>Academic Resource Management System (ARMS)<\/strong> is a web-based application for managing the end-to-end academic resource planning process. The ARMS manages full-time instructor loads including teaching, course releases and sabbaticals\/leaves. In addition the system manages contract faculty allocation and teaching assignments including part-time budget\/complement, postings, notice of recommended appointments (NRAs) and offer letters.<\/p>\n<p>The <strong>ARMS<\/strong> has enabled the University to move forward on a number of related initiatives, which themselves have had the effect of improving productivity and quality in administration:<\/p>\n<div>\n<ul>\n<li>Support of an integrated resource planning process<\/li>\n<li>Earlier information to students on who is teaching what<\/li>\n<li>Accurate information to drive detailed on-line course evaluation<\/li>\n<li>Earlier instructor access to learning management systems<\/li>\n<li>Supporting the University\u2019s emergency preparedness and sustainability plans<\/li>\n<li>Support the efficient assembly of enterprise data on teaching for the institutional data warehouse<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/div>\n<div>\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong>ARMS<\/strong> has been integrated with Oracle PeopleSoft HCM to enable the system to handle entering payroll information directly, completing the graduate student and contract faculty end-to-end hiring process. The system has contributed to a culture of transparency and accountability across all Faculties, Departments and Units.<\/p>\n<p align=\"justify\">